PP22PP() -- Memory-Manipulation Routine

PP22PP(_g_l__a_d_d_r)
vvaaddddrr_tt _g_l__a_d_d_r;

Macro  PP22PP converts  a system  global address to  a physical  address.  For
example, the code sequence

    #include <sys/mmu.h>
    phys_addr = P2P(sys_gl_addr);

converts  system global  address _s_y_s__g_l__a_d_d_r  and  stores it  into variable
_p_h_y_s__a_d_d_r.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
mmeemmoorryy-mmaanniippuullaattiioonn rroouuttiinneess
